    <category>
        <pattern>ENVIRONMENTAL MITIGATION STRATEGIES</pattern>
        <template>
            üåø **Environmental Mitigation Strategies**:
            - **Fish Ladders**: Structures that allow fish to bypass dams.
            - **Environmental Flow Releases**: Maintaining natural river flow patterns to support ecosystems.
            - **Habitat Restoration**: Rehabilitating areas affected by hydropower projects.
            - **Sediment Management**: Regularly removing sediment buildup to maintain reservoir capacity.
            - **Community Engagement**: Involving local communities in planning and decision-making processes.
        </template>
    </category>

